Morphological analyses were done either using light or scanning electron microscopy. Specimens were prepared as follows: adult flies stored in 70% ETOH were completely dehydrated via sequential washes with 80%, 90%, 95% and 100% ETOH. These specimens were then critical point dried using standard protocols (
Grimaldi 1987
). Male genitalic structures were dissected from the abdomen and adhered to a specimen mount (Ted Pella, Inc.) using double coated, carbon conductive tabs (Ted Pella, Inc.). The material was sputter coated and visualized using a Hitachi S4700 Field Emission Scanning Electron Microscope. All image files were saved in.tif file format and edited in Adobe Photoshop 5.0 (Adobe Systems, Inc.). Image files are available upon request.
